Adds a new stop, defined by an offset and a color, to the gradient. If the offset is
 not between 0 and 1, an INDEX_SIZE_ERR is returned, if the color can't be parsed as a
 CSS <color>, a SYNTAX_ERR is returned.

defs.name: get_height
defs.docs: Returns the number of rows in the image data object.

defs.name: get_width
defs.docs: Returns the number of pixels per row in the image data object.

defs.name: get_canvas
defs.docs:
The CanvasRenderingContext2D.canvas property is a read-only reference to the HTMLCanvasElement
 object that is associated with the context. It might be null if there is no association with an <canvas> element.

defs.name: get_fill_style
defs.docs:
The CanvasRenderingContext2D.fillStyle property of the Canvas 2D API specifies the color or style to use inside shapes.
 The default is #000 (black).

defs.name: set_fill_style_color
defs.docs:
The CanvasRenderingContext2D.fillStyle property of the Canvas 2D API specifies the color or style to use inside shapes.
 The default is #000 (black).

defs.name: set_fill_style_gradient
defs.docs:
The CanvasRenderingContext2D.fillStyle property of the Canvas 2D API specifies the color or style to use inside shapes.
 The default is #000 (black).

defs.name: set_fill_style_pattern
defs.docs:
The CanvasRenderingContext2D.fillStyle property of the Canvas 2D API specifies the color or style to use inside shapes.
 The default is #000 (black).

defs.name: get_font
defs.docs:
The CanvasRenderingContext2D.font property of the Canvas 2D API specifies the current
 text style being used when drawing text. This string uses the same syntax as the CSS
 font specifier. The default font is 10px sans-serif.

defs.name: set_font
defs.docs:
The CanvasRenderingContext2D.font property of the Canvas 2D API specifies the current
 text style being used when drawing text. This string uses the same syntax as the CSS
 font specifier. The default font is 10px sans-serif.

defs.name: get_global_alpha
defs.docs:
The CanvasRenderingContext2D.globalAlpha property of the Canvas 2D API specifies the alpha
 value that is applied to shapes and images before they are drawn onto the canvas.
 The value is in the range from 0.0 (fully transparent) to 1.0 (fully opaque).

defs.name: set_global_alpha
defs.docs:
The CanvasRenderingContext2D.globalAlpha property of the Canvas 2D API specifies the alpha
 value that is applied to shapes and images before they are drawn onto the canvas.
 The value is in the range from 0.0 (fully transparent) to 1.0 (fully opaque).

defs.name: get_global_composite_operation
defs.docs:
The CanvasRenderingContext2D.globalCompositeOperation property of the Canvas 2D API sets the
 type of compositing operation to apply when drawing new shapes, where type is a string identifying
 which of the compositing or blending mode operations to use.

defs.name: set_global_composite_operation
defs.docs:
The CanvasRenderingContext2D.globalCompositeOperation property of the Canvas 2D API sets the
 type of compositing operation to apply when drawing new shapes, where type is a string identifying
 which of the compositing or blending mode operations to use.

defs.name: get_line_cap
defs.docs:
Determines how the end points of every line are drawn.
 There are three possible values for this property and those are: butt, round and square.
 By default this property is set to butt.

defs.name: set_line_cap
defs.docs:
Determines how the end points of every line are drawn.
 There are three possible values for this property and those are: butt, round and square.
 By default this property is set to butt.

defs.name: get_line_dash_offset
defs.docs: Sets the line dash pattern offset or "phase" to achieve a "marching ants" effect, for example.

defs.name: set_line_dash_offset
defs.docs: Sets the line dash pattern offset or "phase" to achieve a "marching ants" effect, for example.

defs.name: get_line_join
defs.docs:
Determines how two connecting segments (of lines, arcs or curves) with non-zero lengths in a shape are
 joined together (degenerate segments with zero lengths, whose specified endpoints and control points are
 exactly at the same position, are skipped).

defs.name: set_line_join
defs.docs:
Determines how two connecting segments (of lines, arcs or curves) with non-zero lengths in a shape are
 joined together (degenerate segments with zero lengths, whose specified endpoints and control points are
 exactly at the same position, are skipped).

defs.name: get_line_width
defs.docs:
Sets the thickness of lines in space units. When getting, it returns the current value (1.0 by default).
 When setting, zero, negative, Infinity and NaN values are ignored; otherwise the current value is set to the new value.

defs.name: set_line_width
defs.docs:
Sets the thickness of lines in space units. When getting, it returns the current value (1.0 by default).
 When setting, zero, negative, Infinity and NaN values are ignored; otherwise the current value is set to the new value.

defs.name: get_miter_limit
defs.docs:
sets the miter limit ratio in space units. When getting, it returns the current value (10.0 by default).
 When setting, zero, negative, Infinity and NaN values are ignored; otherwise the current value is set to the new value.

defs.name: set_miter_limit
defs.docs:
sets the miter limit ratio in space units. When getting, it returns the current value (10.0 by default).
 When setting, zero, negative, Infinity and NaN values are ignored; otherwise the current value is set to the new value.

defs.name: get_shadow_blur
defs.docs:
Specifies the level of the blurring effect; this value doesn't correspond to a number of pixels and is not
 affected by the current transformation matrix. The default value is 0.

defs.name: set_shadow_blur
defs.docs:
Specifies the level of the blurring effect; this value doesn't correspond to a number of pixels and is not
 affected by the current transformation matrix. The default value is 0.

defs.name: get_shadow_color
defs.docs: Specifies the color of the shadow.

defs.name: set_shadow_color
defs.docs: Specifies the color of the shadow.

defs.name: get_shadow_offset_x
defs.docs: Specifies the distance that the shadow will be offset in horizontal distance.

defs.name: set_shadow_offset_x
defs.docs: Specifies the distance that the shadow will be offset in horizontal distance.

defs.name: get_shadow_offset_y
defs.docs: Specifies the distance that the shadow will be offset in vertical distance.

defs.name: set_shadow_offset_y
defs.docs: Specifies the distance that the shadow will be offset in vertical distance.

defs.name: get_stroke_style
defs.docs: Specifies the color or style to use for the lines around shapes. The default is #000 (black).

defs.name: set_stroke_style_color
defs.docs: Specifies the color or style to use for the lines around shapes. The default is #000 (black).

defs.name: set_stroke_style_gradient
defs.docs: Specifies the color or style to use for the lines around shapes. The default is #000 (black).

defs.name: set_stroke_style_pattern
defs.docs: Specifies the color or style to use for the lines around shapes. The default is #000 (black).

defs.name: get_text_align
defs.docs:
specifies the current text alignment being used when drawing text.
 Beware that the alignment is based on the x value of the fillText() method.
 So if textAlign is "center", then the text would be drawn at x - (width / 2).

defs.name: set_text_align
defs.docs:
specifies the current text alignment being used when drawing text.
 Beware that the alignment is based on the x value of the fillText() method.
 So if textAlign is "center", then the text would be drawn at x - (width / 2).

defs.name: get_text_baseline
defs.docs: Specifies the current text baseline being used when drawing text.

defs.name: set_text_baseline
defs.docs: Specifies the current text baseline being used when drawing text.

defs.name: arc
defs.value: fn (&self, x: f64, y: f64, radius: f64, start_angle: f64, end_angle: f64, anticlockwise: bool) -> ()
defs.docs:
Adds an arc to the path which is centered at (x, y) position with radius r starting
 at startAngle and ending at endAngle going in the given direction by anticlockwise
 (defaulting to clockwise).

defs.name: arc_to
defs.value: fn (&self, x1: f64, y1: f64, x2: f64, y2: f64, radius: f64) -> Result<(), IndexSizeError>
defs.docs:
Adds an arc to the path with the given control points and radius.
 The arc drawn will be a part of a circle, never elliptical.
 Typical use could be making a rounded corner.
 One way to think about the arc drawn is to imagine two straight segments, from the
 starting point (latest point in current path) to the first control point, and then
 from the first control point to the second control point. These two segments form
 a sharp corner with the first control point being in the corner. Using arcTo, the
 corner will instead be an arc with the given radius.
 The arc is tangential to both segments, which can sometimes produce surprising results,
 e.g. if the radius given is larger than the distance between the starting point and the first control point.
 If the radius specified doesn't make the arc meet the starting point (latest point in the current path),
 the starting point is connected to the arc with a straight line segment.

defs.name: begin_path
defs.docs: Starts a new path by emptying the list of sub-paths. Call this method when you want to create a new path.

defs.name: bezier_curve_to
defs.value: fn (&self, cp1x: f64, cp1y: f64, cp2x: f64, cp2y: f64, x: f64, y: f64) -> ()
defs.docs:
Adds a cubic Bzier curve to the path. It requires three points. The first two points
 are control points and the third one is the end point. The starting point is the last
 point in the current path, which can be changed using moveTo() before creating the Bzier curve.

defs.name: clear_rect
defs.value: fn (&self, x: f64, y: f64, width: f64, height: f64) -> ()
defs.docs:
Sets all pixels in the rectangle defined by starting point (x, y) and size (width, height)
 to transparent black, erasing any previously drawn content.

defs.name: clip
defs.docs:
Turns the path currently being built into the current clipping path.
 ctx.clip(path, fillRule) is not supported because [(Path2D)](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Path2D) is still experimental

defs.name: close_path
defs.docs:
Causes the point of the pen to move back to the start of the current sub-path. It tries
 to add a straight line (but does not actually draw it) from the current point to the start.
 If the shape has already been closed or has only one point, this function does nothing.

defs.name: create_linear_gradient
defs.value: fn (&self, x0: f64, y0: f64, x1: f64, y1: f64) -> CanvasGradient
defs.docs: Creates a gradient along the line given by the coordinates represented by the parameters.

defs.name: create_image_data
defs.value: fn (&self, width: f64, height: f64) -> Result<ImageData, IndexSizeError>
defs.docs:
Creates a new, blank ImageData object with the specified dimensions.
 All of the pixels in the new object are transparent black.

defs.name: create_image_data_size_of
defs.docs:
Creates a new, blank ImageData object with the specified dimensions.
 All of the pixels in the new object are transparent black.

defs.name: create_pattern_image
defs.value: fn (&self, image: ImageElement, repetition: Repetition) -> CanvasPattern
defs.docs:
Creates a pattern using the specified image (a CanvasImageSource). It repeats the source in
 the directions specified by the repetition argument. This method returns a CanvasPattern.

defs.name: create_radial_gradient
defs.value: fn (&self, x0: f64, y0: f64, r0: f64, x1: f64, y1: f64, r1: f64) -> Result<CanvasGradient, IndexSizeError>
defs.docs:
Creates a radial gradient given by the coordinates of the two circles represented by the parameters.
 This method returns a CanvasGradient.

defs.name: draw_focus_if_needed
defs.docs: Draws a focus ring around the current path or given path, If a given element is focused.

defs.name: draw_image
defs.value: fn (&self, image: ImageElement, dx: f64, dy: f64) -> Result<(), DrawImageError>
defs.docs: Provides different ways to draw an image onto the canvas.

defs.name: draw_image_d
defs.value: fn (&self, image: ImageElement, dx: f64, dy: f64, d_width: f64, d_height: f64) -> Result<(), DrawImageError>
defs.docs: Provides different ways to draw an image onto the canvas.

defs.name: draw_image_s
defs.value: fn (&self, image: ImageElement, sx: f64, sy: f64, s_width: f64, s_height: f64, dx: f64, dy: f64, d_width: f64, d_height: f64) -> Result<(), DrawImageError>
defs.docs: Provides different ways to draw an image onto the canvas.

defs.name: fill
defs.docs: Fills the current or given path with the current fill style using the non-zero or even-odd winding rule.

defs.name: fill_rect
defs.value: fn (&self, x: f64, y: f64, width: f64, height: f64) -> ()
defs.docs:
Draws a filled rectangle whose starting point is at the coordinates (x, y) with the
 specified width and height and whose style is determined by the fillStyle attribute.

defs.name: fill_text
defs.value: fn (&self, text: &str, x: f64, y: f64, max_width: Option<f64>) -> ()
defs.docs:
Draws a text string at the specified coordinates, filling the string's characters
 with the current foreground color. An optional parameter allows specifying a maximum
 width for the rendered text, which the user agent will achieve by condensing the
 text or by using a lower font size.

defs.name: get_image_data
defs.value: fn (&self, sx: f64, sy: f64, sw: f64, sh: f64) -> Result<ImageData, GetImageDataError>
defs.docs:
Returns an ImageData object representing the underlying pixel data for the area of the
 canvas denoted by the rectangle which starts at (sx, sy) and has an sw width and sh height.
 This method is not affected by the canvas transformation matrix.
 Pixels outside of the canvas area are present as transparent black values in the returned ImageData.

defs.name: get_line_dash
defs.docs: Gets the current line dash pattern.

defs.name: is_point_in_path
defs.value: fn (&self, x: f64, y: f64, fill_rule: FillRule) -> bool
defs.docs: Reports whether or not the specified point is contained in the current path.

defs.name: is_point_in_stroke
defs.value: fn (&self, x: f64, y: f64) -> bool
defs.docs: Reports whether or not the specified point is inside the area contained by the stroking of a path.

defs.name: line_to
defs.docs: Connects the last point in the sub-path to the x, y coordinates with a straight line (but does not actually draw it).

defs.name: measure_text
defs.docs: Returns a TextMetrics object that contains information about the measured text (such as its width for example).

defs.name: move_to
defs.docs: Moves the starting point of a new sub-path to the (x, y) coordinates.

defs.name: put_image_data
defs.value: fn (&self, image_data: ImageData, dx: f32, dy: f32) -> Result<(), InvalidStateError>
defs.docs:
Paints data from the given ImageData object onto the bitmap. If a dirty rectangle is provided, only the pixels
 from that rectangle are painted. This method is not affected by the canvas transformation matrix.

defs.name: put_image_data_dirty
defs.value: fn (&self, image_data: ImageData, dx: f32, dy: f32, dirty_x: f32, dirty_y: f32, dirty_width: f32, dirty_height: f32) -> Result<(), InvalidStateError>
defs.docs:
Paints data from the given ImageData object onto the bitmap. If a dirty rectangle is provided, only the pixels
 from that rectangle are painted. This method is not affected by the canvas transformation matrix.

defs.name: quadratic_curve_to
defs.value: fn (&self, cpx: f64, cpy: f64, x: f64, y: f64) -> ()
defs.docs:
Adds a quadratic Bzier curve to the path. It requires two points.
 The first point is a control point and the second one is the end point.
 The starting point is the last point in the current path, which can be changed using
 moveTo() before creating the quadratic Bzier curve.

defs.name: rect
defs.value: fn (&self, x: f64, y: f64, width: f64, height: f64) -> ()
defs.docs:
Creates a path for a rectangle at position (x, y) with a size that is determined by width and height.
 Those four points are connected by straight lines and the sub-path is marked as closed,
 so that you can fill or stroke this rectangle.

defs.name: restore
defs.docs:
Restores the most recently saved canvas state by popping the top entry in the drawing state stack.
 If there is no saved state, this method does nothing.

defs.name: rotate
defs.docs: Adds a rotation to the transformation matrix. The angle argument represents a clockwise rotation angle and is expressed in radians.

defs.name: save
defs.docs: Saves the entire state of the canvas by pushing the current state onto a stack.

defs.name: scale
defs.docs:
adds a scaling transformation to the canvas units by x horizontally and by y vertically.
 By default, one unit on the canvas is exactly one pixel. If we apply, for instance, a scaling factor of 0.5,
 the resulting unit would become 0.5 pixels and so shapes would be drawn at half size.
 In a similar way setting the scaling factor to 2.0 would increase the unit size and one unit now becomes two pixels.
 This results in shapes being drawn twice as large.

defs.name: set_line_dash
defs.docs: Sets the line dash pattern used when stroking lines, using an array of values which specify alternating lengths of lines and gaps which describe the pattern.

defs.name: set_transform
defs.docs:
Resets (overrides) the current transformation to the identity matrix and then invokes a transformation described by the arguments of this method.
 See also the transform() method, which does not override the current transform matrix and multiplies it with a given one.

defs.name: stroke
defs.docs: Strokes the current or given path with the current stroke style using the non-zero winding rule.

defs.name: stroke_rect
defs.value: fn (&self, x: f64, y: f64, width: f64, height: f64) -> ()
defs.docs: Paints a rectangle which has a starting point at (x, y) and has a w width and an h height onto the canvas, using the current stroke style.

defs.name: stroke_text
defs.value: fn (&self, text: &str, x: f64, y: f64, max_width: Option<f64>) -> ()
defs.docs:
Strokes  that is, draws the outlines of  the characters of a specified text string at the given (x, y) position.
 If the optional fourth parameter for a maximum width is provided, the text is scaled to fit that width.
 See the CanvasRenderingContext2D.fillText() method to draw the text with the characters filled with color rather than having just their outlines drawn.

defs.name: transform
defs.docs:
Multiplies the current transformation with the matrix described by the arguments of this method.
 You are able to scale, rotate, move and skew the context.
 See also the setTransform() method which resets the current transform to the identity matrix and then invokes transform().

defs.name: translate
defs.docs: Adds a translation transformation by moving the canvas and its origin x horizontally and y vertically on the grid.

defs.name: get_width
defs.docs: Contains the text's advance width (the width of that inline box) in CSS pixels.

defs.name: MutationObserver
defs.docs: Provides a way to receive notifications about changes to the DOM.

defs.name: MutationObserverInit
defs.value: MutationObserverInit { child_list, attributes, character_data, subtree, attribute_old_value, character_data_old_value, attribute_filter }
defs.docs: Specifies which changes should be observed for the target.

defs.name: child_list
defs.docs: If `true` it will observe all inserts and removals of the target's children (including text nodes).

defs.name: attributes
defs.docs: If `true` it will observe all changes to the target's attributes.

defs.name: character_data
defs.docs: If `true` it will observe all changes to the `CharacterData`'s data.

defs.name: subtree
defs.docs: If `true` it will observe all changes to the target, the target's children, and the target's sub-children.

defs.name: attribute_old_value
defs.docs: If `true` it will store the target's old attribute value in [`old_value`](enum.MutationRecord.html#variant.Attribute.field.old_value).

defs.name: character_data_old_value
defs.docs: If `true` it will store the `CharacterData`'s old data in [`old_data`](enum.MutationRecord.html#variant.CharacterData.field.old_data).

defs.name: attribute_filter
defs.docs: If `Some` it will only observe the specified attributes. The attributes should be specified without a namespace.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Returns a new [`MutationObserverHandle`](struct.MutationObserverHandle.html) with the given callback.

defs.name: observe
defs.value: fn <T> (&self, target: &T, options: MutationObserverInit) -> Result<(), TODO>
defs.docs: Starts observing changes to the `target`.

defs.name: disconnect
defs.docs: Stops observing all targets.

defs.name: take_records
defs.docs: Empties the `MutationObserver`'s record queue and returns what was in there.

defs.name: MutationObserverHandle
defs.docs: A wrapper which ensures that memory is properly cleaned up when it's no longer needed.

defs.name: Attribute
defs.docs: One of the target's attributes was changed.

defs.name: CharacterData
defs.docs: The target's data was changed.

defs.name: ChildList
defs.value: MutationRecord::ChildList { target, inserted_nodes, removed_nodes, previous_sibling, next_sibling }
defs.docs: The children of the target were changed.

defs.name: MutationRecord
defs.docs: Contains information about an individual change to the DOM.

defs.name: IError
defs.docs:
Represents the JavaScript `Error` interface. An `Error` is thrown whenever a run-time error
 occurs.

defs.name: message
defs.docs: Returns a human-readable description of the error.

defs.name: name
defs.docs: Returns a name specifiying the type of error.

defs.name: Error
defs.docs:
A reference to a JavaScript `Error` object. An `Error` is thrown whenever a run-time error
 occurs.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates a new `Error` with the specified `description`.

defs.name: TypeError
defs.docs: Used to indicate an unsuccessful operation when none of the other NativeError objects are an appropriate indication of the failure cause.

defs.name: Touch
defs.docs:
The Touch interface represents a single contact point on a touch-sensitive
 device. The contact point is commonly a finger or stylus and the device may
 be a touchscreen or trackpad.

defs.name: identifier
defs.docs:
Returns a unique identifier for this Touch object. A given touch point
 (say, by a finger) will have the same identifier for the duration of
 its movement around the surface. This lets you ensure that you're
 tracking the same touch all the time.

defs.name: screen_x
defs.docs: Returns the X coordinate of the touch point relative to the left edge of the screen.

defs.name: screen_y
defs.docs: Returns the Y coordinate of the touch point relative to the left edge of the screen.

defs.name: client_x
defs.docs: Returns the X coordinate of the touch point relative to the left edge of the browser viewport, not including any scroll offset.

defs.name: client_y
defs.docs: Returns the Y coordinate of the touch point relative to the left edge of the browser viewport, not including any scroll offset.

defs.name: page_x
defs.docs: Returns the X coordinate of the touch point relative to the left edge of the document. Unlike clientX, this value includes the horizontal scroll offset, if any.

defs.name: page_y
defs.docs: Returns the Y coordinate of the touch point relative to the left edge of the document. Unlike clientX, this value includes the horizontal scroll offset, if any.

defs.name: target
defs.docs: Returns the Element on which the touch point started when it was first placed on the surface, even if the touch point has since moved outside the interactive area of that element or even been removed from the document.

defs.name: radius_x
defs.docs: Returns the X radius of the ellipse that most closely circumscribes the area of contact with the screen. The value is in pixels of the same scale as screenX.

defs.name: radius_y
defs.docs: Returns the Y radius of the ellipse that most closely circumscribes the area of contact with the screen. The value is in pixels of the same scale as screenY.

defs.name: rotation_angle
defs.docs: Returns the angle (in degrees) that the ellipse described by radiusX and radiusY must be rotated, clockwise, to most accurately cover the area of contact between the user and the surface.

defs.name: force
defs.docs: Returns the amount of pressure being applied to the surface by the user, as a float between 0.0 (no pressure) and 1.0 (maximum pressure).

defs.name: altitude_angle
defs.docs: The altitude (in radians) of a stylus, in the range 0 (parallel to the surface) to /2 (perpendicular to the surface). The value 0 should be used for devices which do not support this property.

defs.name: azimuth_angle
defs.docs: The azimuth angle (in radians) of a stylus, in the range 0 to 2. 0 represents a stylus whose cap is pointing in the direction of increasing screenX values. /2 represents a stylus whose cap is pointing in the direction of increasing screenY values. The value 0 should be used for devices which do not support this property.

defs.name: touch_type
defs.docs: The type of device used to trigger the touch.

defs.name: Direct
defs.docs: A direct touch from a finger on the screen.

defs.name: Stylus
defs.docs: A touch from a stylus or pen device.

defs.name: TouchType
defs.docs: An enumeration representing the different types of possible touch input.

defs.name: IDomException
defs.docs:
The `IDomException` interface represents an abnormal event which occurs as the result of
 calling a web API.

defs.name: DomException
defs.docs: A reference to a JavaScript `DOMException` object.

defs.name: HierarchyRequestError
defs.docs: Occurs when an operation would result in an incorrect node tree.

defs.name: InvalidAccessError
defs.docs: Occurs when an object does not support an operation or argument.

defs.name: NoModificationAllowedError
defs.docs: Occurs when the object can not be modified.

defs.name: NotFoundError
defs.docs: Occurs when the specified object cannot be found.

defs.name: SecurityError
defs.docs: Occurs when the requested operation is insecure.

defs.name: SyntaxError
defs.docs: Occurs when an argument does not match the expected pattern.

defs.name: IndexSizeError
defs.docs: Occurs when an argument is out of range.

defs.name: InvalidStateError
defs.docs: Occurs when an object is in an invalid state.

defs.name: NotSupportedError
defs.docs: Used to indicate an unsuccessful operation when none of the other NativeError objects are an appropriate indication of the failure cause.

defs.name: InvalidCharacterError
defs.docs: Used to indicate the string contains one or more characters which are invalid.

defs.name: InvalidPointerId
defs.docs: Used to indicate that a pointer id passed as an argument was for some reason invalid.

defs.name: AbortError
defs.docs: Used to indicate that the operation was aborted.

defs.name: NamespaceError
defs.docs: Indicates an xml namespace-related feature was used incorrectly.

defs.name: ChangeEvent
defs.docs:
The `ChangeEvent` is fired for input, select, and textarea
 elements when a change to the element's value is committed
 by the user. Unlike the input event, the change event is not
 necessarily fired for each change to an element's value.

defs.name: InputEvent
defs.docs:
The `InputEvent` is fired synchronously when the value of an
 input, select, or textarea element is changed. For input elements
 with type=checkbox or type=radio, the input event should fire when
 a user toggles the control (via touch, mouse or keyboard) per the
 HTML5 specification, but historically, this has not been the case.
 Check compatibility, or attach to the change event instead for
 elements of these types.

defs.name: ResourceLoadEvent
defs.docs: The `ResourceLoadEvent` is fired when a resource and its dependent resources have finished loading.

defs.name: ResourceAbortEvent
defs.docs: The `ResourceAbortEvent` is fired when the loading of a resource has been aborted.

defs.name: ResourceErrorEvent
defs.docs:
The `ResourceErrorEvent` is fired when an error occurred; the exact circumstances vary,
 since this event is used from a variety of APIs.

defs.name: ResizeEvent
defs.docs: The resize event is fired when the document view has been resized.

defs.name: ScrollEvent
defs.docs: The scroll event is fired when the document view or an element has been scrolled.

defs.name: ReadyStateChangeEvent
defs.docs: The readystatechange event is fired when the readyState attribute of a document has changed.

defs.name: SubmitEvent
defs.docs: The submit event is fired when a form is submitted.

defs.name: SelectionChangeEvent
defs.docs:
The selectionchange event of the Selection API is fired when the current text selection on a
 document is changed.

defs.name: IDragEvent
defs.docs:
The DragEvent interface is a DOM event that represents a drag and drop interaction.
 The user initiates a drag by placing a pointer device (such as a mouse) on the touch surface
 and then dragging the pointer to a new location (such as another DOM element).

defs.name: data_transfer
defs.docs: The DataEvent.dataTransfer property holds the drag operation's data (as a DataTransfer object).

defs.name: DragRelatedEvent
defs.docs:
A reference to a JavaScript object which implements the [IDragEvent](trait.IDragEvent.html)
 interface.

defs.name: DragEvent
defs.docs:
The drag event is fired every few hundred milliseconds as an element or text selection is being
 dragged by the user.

defs.name: DragStartEvent
defs.docs: The dragstart event is fired when the user starts dragging an element or text selection.

defs.name: DragEnterEvent
defs.docs: The dragenter event is fired when a dragged element or text selection enters a valid drop target.

defs.name: DragExitEvent
defs.docs:
The dragexit event is fired when an element is no longer the drag operation's immediate
 selection target.

defs.name: DragLeaveEvent
defs.docs: The dragleave event is fired when a dragged element or text selection leaves a valid drop target.

defs.name: DragOverEvent
defs.docs:
The dragover event is fired when an element or text selection is being dragged over a valid drop
 target (every few hundred milliseconds).

defs.name: DragDropEvent
defs.docs: The drop event is fired when an element or text selection is dropped on a valid drop target.

defs.name: DragEndEvent
defs.docs:
The dragend event is fired when a drag operation is being ended (by releasing a mouse button or
 hitting the escape key).

defs.name: DataTransfer
defs.docs:
The DataTransfer object is used to hold the data that is being dragged during a drag and drop
 operation.

defs.name: drop_effect
defs.docs:
Gets the type of drag-and-drop operation currently selected type.
 The value must be none, copy, link or move.

defs.name: set_drop_effect
defs.docs:
Sets the type of drag-and-drop operation currently selected.
 The value must be none, copy, link or move.

defs.name: effect_allowed
defs.docs:
Provides all of the types of operations that are possible.
 Must be one of none, copy, copyLink, copyMove, link, linkMove, move, all or uninitialized.

defs.name: set_effect_allowed
defs.docs:
Sets the effect that is allowed for a drag operation.
 Must be one of none, copy, copyLink, copyMove, link, linkMove, move, all or uninitialized.

defs.name: items
defs.docs: Gives a DataTransferItemList object which is a list of all of the drag data.

defs.name: files
defs.docs:
Contains a list of all the local files available on the data transfer.
 If the drag operation doesn't involve dragging files, this property is an empty list.

defs.name: types
defs.docs: An array of strings giving the formats that were set in the dragstart event.

defs.name: clear_data
defs.docs:
Remove the data associated with a given type. The type argument is optional.
 If the type is empty or not specified, the data associated with all types is removed.
 If data for the specified type does not exist, or the data transfer contains no data,
 this method will have no effect.

defs.name: get_data
defs.docs:
Retrieves the data for a given type, or an empty string if data for that type does not exist
 or the data transfer contains no data.

defs.name: set_data
defs.docs:
Set the data for a given type.
 If data for the type does not exist, it is added at the end, such that the last item in the
 types list will be the new format.
 If data for the type already exists, the existing data is replaced in the same position.

defs.name: set_drag_image
defs.value: fn (&self, img: &ImageElement, x_offset: i32, y_offset: i32) -> ()
defs.docs: Set the image to be used for dragging if a custom one is desired.

defs.name: Copy
defs.docs: A copy of the source item is made at the new location

defs.name: Move
defs.docs: An item is moved to a new location.

defs.name: Link
defs.docs: A link is established to the source at the new location.

defs.name: None
defs.docs: The item may not be dropped.

defs.name: DropEffect
defs.docs: A DOMString representing the drag operation effect.

defs.name: None
defs.docs: The item may not be dropped.

defs.name: Copy
defs.docs: A copy of the source item may be made at the new location.

defs.name: CopyLink
defs.docs: A copy or link operation is permitted.

defs.name: CopyMove
defs.docs: A copy or move operation is permitted.

defs.name: Link
defs.docs: A link may be established to the source at the new location.

defs.name: LinkMove
defs.docs: A link or move operation is permitted.

defs.name: Move
defs.docs: An item may be moved to a new location.

defs.name: All
defs.docs: All operations are permitted.

defs.name: Uninitialized
defs.docs: The default value when the effect has not been set, equivalent to all.

defs.name: EffectAllowed
defs.value: EffectAllowed::{None, Copy, CopyLink, CopyMove, Link, LinkMove, Move, All, Uninitialized}
defs.docs: A DOMString representing the drag operation that is allowed.

defs.name: DataTransferItemList
defs.docs:
The DataTransferItemList object is a list of DataTransferItem objects representing items being
 dragged.
 During a drag operation, each DragEvent has a dataTransfer property and that property is a
 DataTransferItemList.

defs.name: len
defs.docs: An unsigned long that is the number of drag items in the list.

defs.name: add_string
defs.docs:
Adds an item of kind "string" to the drag item list and returns
 a DataTransferItem object for the new item.

defs.name: add_file
defs.docs:
Adds an item of kind "file" to the drag item list and returns
 a DataTransferItem object for the new item.

defs.name: remove
defs.docs: Removes the drag item from the list at the given index.

defs.name: clear
defs.docs: Removes all of the drag items from the list.

defs.name: index
defs.docs: Getter that returns a DataTransferItem at the given index.

defs.name: iter
defs.docs: Returns an iterator over the list

defs.name: DataTransferItem
defs.docs:
The DataTransferItem object represents one drag data item. During a drag operation, each drag
 event has a dataTransfer property which contains a list of drag data items. Each item in the
 list is a DataTransferItem object.

defs.name: kind
defs.docs: The kind of drag data item, string or file.

defs.name: ty
defs.docs: The drag data item's type, typically a MIME type.

defs.name: get_as_file
defs.docs:
Returns the File object associated with the drag data item
 (or null if the drag item is not a file)

defs.name: get_as_string
defs.docs: Invokes the specified callback with the drag data item string as its argument.

defs.name: File
defs.docs: If the drag data item is a file.

defs.name: String
defs.docs: If the kind of drag data item is a plain Unicode string.

defs.name: __Other
defs.docs: If the kind of drag data is something different (e.g. dragging an tag in Firefox)

defs.name: DataTransferItemKind
defs.docs: The kind of drag data item, string or file.

defs.name: as_str
defs.docs:
Returns the string representation of this DataTransferItemKind
 Useful in case the browser returns a non-standard kind that you want to special case.

defs.name: IFocusEvent
defs.docs:
The `IFocusEvent` interface represents focus-related
 events.

defs.name: related_target
defs.docs: Returns the secondary target of this event, if any.

defs.name: FocusRelatedEvent
defs.docs:
A reference to a JavaScript object which implements the [IFocusEvent](trait.IFocusEvent.html)
 interface.

defs.name: FocusEvent
defs.docs:
The `FocusEvent` is fired when an element has received focus. The main
 difference between this event and focusin is that only the latter bubbles.

defs.name: BlurEvent
defs.docs:
The `BlurEvent` is fired when an element has lost focus. The main difference
 between this event and focusout is that only the latter bubbles.

defs.name: IGamepadEvent
defs.docs: A GamepadEvent is fired on the window object, when a gamepad is connected or disconnected to the system.

defs.name: gamepad
defs.docs: Returns the gamepad associated with this event.

defs.name: GamepadEvent
defs.docs:
A reference to a JavaScript object which implements the [IGamepadEvent](trait.IGamepadEvent.html)
 interface.

defs.name: GamepadConnectedEvent
defs.docs: The `GamepadConnected` event is fired on the window object, when the first input is received for a gamepad.

defs.name: GamepadDisconnectedEvent
defs.docs: The `GamepadDisconnected` event is fired on the window object, when a gamepad is disconnected.

defs.name: HashChangeEvent
defs.docs:
The `HashChangeEvent` is fired when the fragment
 identifier of the URL has changed (the part of the URL
 that follows the # symbol, including the # symbol).

defs.name: old_url
defs.docs: The previous URL from which the window was navigated.

defs.name: new_url
defs.docs: The new URL to which the window was navigated.

defs.name: PopStateEvent
defs.docs:
A `PopStateEvent` is dispatched to the window every time the active history entry changes
 between two history entries for the same document. If the history entry being activated was
 created by a call to `history.push_state()` or was affected by a call to
 `history.replace_state()`, the `PopStateEvent`'s state property contains a copy of the history
 entry's state object.

defs.name: state
defs.docs:
The state object associated to the new history entry, if that entry was created with
 push_state or affected by replace_state.

defs.name: IKeyboardEvent
defs.docs:
`IKeyboardEvent` objects describe a user interaction with the
 keyboard. Each event describes a key; the event type identifies
 what kind of activity was performed.

defs.name: alt_key
defs.docs: Indicates whether the Alt key was down when this event was fired.

defs.name: code
defs.docs: Returns a code value that indicates the physical key pressed on the keyboard.

defs.name: ctrl_key
defs.docs: Returns whether the Ctrl key was down when this event was fired.

defs.name: get_modifier_state
defs.docs: Returns whether a modifier key was down when this event was fired.

defs.name: is_composing
defs.docs: Returns whether this event was fired during composition.

defs.name: location
defs.docs: Returns the location of the key on the keyboard.

defs.name: key
defs.docs: Returns the value of a key or keys pressed by the user.

defs.name: meta_key
defs.docs: Indicates whether the Meta key was down when this event was fired.

defs.name: repeat
defs.docs: Indicates whether the key is held down such that it is repeating.

defs.name: shift_key
defs.docs: Indicates whether the Shift key was down when this event was fired.

defs.name: ModifierKey
defs.value: ModifierKey::{Alt, AltGr, CapsLock, Ctrl, Function, FunctionLock, Hyper, Meta, NumLock, OS, ScrollLock, Shift, Super, Symbol, SymbolLock}
defs.docs: A modifier key on the keyboard.

defs.name: Standard
defs.docs: The key has only one version, or the location can't be distinguished.

defs.name: Left
defs.docs: The left-hand version of a key.

defs.name: Right
defs.docs: The right-hand version of a key.

defs.name: Numpad
defs.docs: The key was on a numeric pad.

defs.name: Mobile
defs.docs: The key was on a mobile device.

defs.name: Joystick
defs.docs: The key was on a joystick.

defs.name: KeyboardLocation
defs.value: KeyboardLocation::{Standard, Left, Right, Numpad, Mobile, Joystick}
defs.docs: The location on the keyboard of a key.

defs.name: KeyboardEvent
defs.docs:
A reference to a JavaScript object which implements the [IKeyboardEvent](trait.IKeyboardEvent.html)
 interface.

defs.name: KeyPressEvent
defs.docs:
The `KeyPressEvent` is fired when a key is pressed down. It's only
 fired for keys which produce a character value.

defs.name: KeyDownEvent
defs.docs:
The `KeyDownEvent` is fired when a key is pressed down.
 Unlike the `KeyPressEvent` event it's also fired for keys which
 do not produce a character value.

defs.name: KeyUpEvent
defs.docs: The `KeyUpEvent` is fired when a key is released.

defs.name: IMouseEvent
defs.docs:
The `IMouseEvent` interface represents events that occur due to the user
 interacting with a pointing device (such as a mouse).

defs.name: alt_key
defs.docs: Returns whether the Alt key was down when this event was fired.

defs.name: button
defs.docs: Indicates the mouse button that fired this event.

defs.name: buttons
defs.docs: Indicates which mouse buttons were down when this event was fired.

defs.name: client_x
defs.docs: Returns the X position in the application's client area where this event occured.

defs.name: client_y
defs.docs: Returns the Y position in the application's client area where this event occured.

defs.name: offset_x
defs.docs: Returns the X position on the target element where this event occured.

defs.name: offset_y
defs.docs: Returns the Y position on the target element where this event occured.

defs.name: ctrl_key
defs.docs: Indicates whether the Ctrl key was down when this event fired.

defs.name: get_modifier_state
defs.docs: Returns the current state of the specified modifier key.

defs.name: meta_key
defs.docs: Indicates whether the Meta key was down when this event fired.

defs.name: movement_x
defs.docs:
Returns the change in X coordinate of the pointer between this event and the previous
 MouseMove event.

defs.name: movement_y
defs.docs:
Returns the change in Y coordinate of the pointer between this event and the previous
 MouseMove event.

defs.name: region
defs.docs: Returns the ID of the hit region affected by the event.

defs.name: related_target
defs.docs: Returns the secondary target of this event, if any.

defs.name: screen_x
defs.docs: Returns the X position of the pointer in screen coordinates.

defs.name: screen_y
defs.docs: Returns the Y position of the pointer in screen coordinates.

defs.name: shift_key
defs.docs: Indicates whether the Shift key was down when this event was fired.

defs.name: Left
defs.docs: The left mouse button.

defs.name: Wheel
defs.docs: The mouse wheel/middle mouse button.

defs.name: Right
defs.docs: The right mouse button.

defs.name: Button4
defs.docs: The fourth mouse button (browser back).

defs.name: Button5
defs.docs: The fifth mouse button (browser forward).

defs.name: MouseButton
defs.docs: Represents buttons on a mouse during mouse events.

defs.name: MouseButtonsState
defs.docs: Represents the state of mouse buttons in a `MouseEvent`.

defs.name: is_down
defs.docs: Check if a [MouseButton](enum.MouseButton.html) is currently pressed

defs.name: MouseEvent
defs.docs:
A reference to a JavaScript object which implements the [IMouseEvent](trait.IMouseEvent.html)
 interface.

defs.name: ClickEvent
defs.docs:
The `ClickEvent` is fired when a pointing device button (usually a
 mouse's primary button) is pressed and released on a single element.

defs.name: AuxClickEvent
defs.docs:
The `AuxClickEvent` event is fired when a non-primary pointing device button
 (e.g. any non-left mouse button) has been pressed and released on an element.

defs.name: ContextMenuEvent
defs.docs:
The `ContextMenuEvent` event is fired when the right button of the mouse is clicked
 (before the context menu is displayed), or when the context menu key is pressed.

defs.name: DoubleClickEvent
defs.docs:
The `DoubleClickEvent` is fired when a pointing device button
 (usually a mouse's primary button) is clicked twice on a single
 element.

defs.name: MouseDownEvent
defs.docs:
The `MouseDownEvent` is fired when a pointing device button is pressed on
 an element.

defs.name: MouseUpEvent
defs.docs:
The `MouseUpEvent` is fired when a pointing device button is released
 over an element.

defs.name: MouseMoveEvent
defs.docs:
The `MouseMoveEvent` is fired when a pointing device (usually a mouse)
 is moved while over an element.

defs.name: MouseOverEvent
defs.docs:
The `MouseOverEvent` is fired when a pointing device (usually a mouse)
 is moved onto the element that has the listener attached or onto one of its children.

defs.name: MouseOutEvent
defs.docs:
The `MouseOutEvent` is fired when a pointing device (usually a mouse)
 is moved off the element that has the listener attached or off one of its children.

defs.name: MouseEnterEvent
defs.docs:
The `MouseEnterEvent` is fired when a pointing device (usually a mouse)
 is moved over the element that has the listener attached.

defs.name: MouseLeaveEvent
defs.docs:
The `MouseLeaveEvent` is fired when a pointing device (usually a mouse)
 is moved out of an element that has the listener attached to it.

defs.name: MouseWheelEvent
defs.docs:
The `MouseWheelEvent` is fired when a pointing device's wheel button (usually a mousewheel)
 is rotated over the element that has the listener attached.

defs.name: delta_x
defs.docs: The change in X of the wheel

defs.name: delta_y
defs.docs: The change in Y of the wheel

defs.name: delta_z
defs.docs: The change in Z of the wheel

defs.name: delta_mode
defs.docs: The unit of measure of change

defs.name: Pixel
defs.docs: The unit of measurement for the delta is pixels

defs.name: Line
defs.docs: The unit of measurement for the delta is lines

defs.name: Page
defs.docs: The unit of measurement for the delta is pages

defs.name: MouseWheelDeltaMode
defs.docs: What unit of measure the mouse wheel delta is in

defs.name: IPointerEvent
defs.docs:
The `IPointerEvent` interface represents the state of a DOM event produced by a pointer
 such as the geometry of the contact point, the device type that generated the event, the
 amount of pressure that was applied on the contact surface, etc.

defs.name: pointer_id
defs.docs: Returns a unique identifier for the pointer causing the event.

defs.name: width
defs.docs: Returns the width, in CSS pixels, of the contact geometry of the pointer.

defs.name: height
defs.docs: Returns the height, in CSS pixels, of the contact geometry of the pointer.

defs.name: pressure
defs.docs: Returns the normalized pressure of the pointer in the range [0, 1]

defs.name: tangential_pressure
defs.docs:
Returns the normalized tangential pressure of the pointer in the range [-1, 1], where 0 is
 the hardware's neutral position

defs.name: tilt_x
defs.docs:
Returns the angle, in the range of [-90, 90] degrees, between the Y-Z plane and the plane
 containing the transducer (e.g. pen stylus) and the Y axis.

defs.name: tilt_y
defs.docs:
Returns the angle, in the range of [-90, 90] degrees, between the X-Z plane and the plane
 containing the transducer (e.g. pen stylus) and the X axis.

defs.name: twist
defs.docs:
Returns the clockwise rotation, in the range of [0, 359] degrees, of
 the transducer (e.g. pen stylus) around it's own major axis

defs.name: pointer_type
defs.docs: Indicates the device type that caused the event.

defs.name: is_primary
defs.docs: Indicates if the pointer represents the primary pointer of this pointer type

defs.name: PointerEvent
defs.docs:
A reference to a JavaScript object which implements the [IPointerEvent](trait.IPointerEvent.html)
 interface.

defs.name: PointerOverEvent
defs.docs:
The `PointerOverEvent` is fired when a pointing device is moved into
 a element's hit test boundaries.

defs.name: PointerEnterEvent
defs.docs:
The `PointerEnterEvent` is fired when a pointing device is moved into
 the hit test boundaries of an element or its descendants. This event does not bubble.

defs.name: PointerDownEvent
defs.docs: The `PointerDownEvent` is fired when a pointer becomes active

defs.name: PointerMoveEvent
defs.docs: The `PointerMoveEvent` is fired when a pointer changes coordinates

defs.name: get_coalesced_events
defs.docs: Returns the sequence of all `PointerEvent` instances that were coalesced into the dispatched `PointerMoveEvent`.

defs.name: PointerUpEvent
defs.docs: The `PointerUpEvent` is fired when a pointer is no longer active

defs.name: PointerCancelEvent
defs.docs:
The `PointerCancelEvent` is fired when a pointer will no longer produce events
 (for example the device is deactivated), or if the pointer starts a gesture after a pointerdown event
 (for example panning, zooming, or drag and drop)

defs.name: PointerOutEvent
defs.docs:
The `PointerOutEvent` is fired when the pointer moves out of the hit test boundaries of an element.
 This can include when a finger leaves a touch screen or a pen leaves the detectable hover range.

defs.name: PointerLeaveEvent
defs.docs:
The `PointerLeaveEvent` is fired when the pointer moves out of the hit test boundaries
 of an element and it's descendants. This can include when a finger leaves a touch screen
 or a pen leaves the detectable hover range. This event does not bubble.

defs.name: GotPointerCaptureEvent
defs.docs: The `GotPointerCaptureEvent` fires when an element receives pointer capture

defs.name: LostPointerCaptureEvent
defs.docs: The `LostPointerCaptureEvent` fires when an element loses pointer capture

defs.name: PointerLockChangeEvent
defs.docs: The `PointerLockChangeEvent` fires when the pointer is locked or unlocked

defs.name: PointerLockErrorEvent
defs.docs: The `PointerLockErrorEvent` fires when an error occurs locking a pointer

defs.name: IProgressEvent
defs.docs:
The `IProgressEvent` interface represents progress-related
 events.

defs.name: length_computable
defs.docs: Indicates whether the progress is measureable.

defs.name: loaded
defs.docs: Returns the amount of work already performed by the underlying process.

defs.name: total
defs.docs: Returns the total amount of work that the underlying process will perform.

defs.name: ProgressRelatedEvent
defs.docs:
A reference to a JavaScript object which implements the [IProgressEvent](trait.IProgressEvent.html)
 interface.

defs.name: ProgressEvent
defs.docs: The `ProgressEvent` is fired to indicate that an operation is in progress.

defs.name: ProgressLoadEvent
defs.docs: The `ProgressLoadEvent` is fired when progress has successful finished.

defs.name: LoadStartEvent
defs.docs: The `LoadStartEvent` is fired when progress has begun.

defs.name: LoadEndEvent
defs.docs:
The `LoadEndEvent` is fired when progress has stopped,
 e.g. after `ProgressErrorEvent`, `ProgressAbortEvent`
 or `ProgressLoadEvent` have been dispatched.

defs.name: ProgressAbortEvent
defs.docs: The `ProgressAbortEvent` is fired when the progress has been aborted.

defs.name: ProgressErrorEvent
defs.docs: The `ProgressErrorEvent` is fired when the progress has failed.

defs.name: SocketCloseEvent
defs.docs: A SocketCloseEvent is sent to clients using WebSockets when the connection is closed.

defs.name: code
defs.docs: Returns the close code sent by the server.

defs.name: reason
defs.docs: Returns the reason the server closed the connection. This is specific to the particular server and sub-protocol.

defs.name: was_clean
defs.docs: Returns whether or not the connection was cleanly closed.

defs.name: SocketErrorEvent
defs.docs:
The error event is fired when an error occurred; the exact circumstances vary,
 events by this name are used from a variety of APIs.

defs.name: SocketOpenEvent
defs.docs: An open event informs the target that a data connection, has been established.

defs.name: Text
defs.docs: Text message

defs.name: Blob
defs.docs: Binary message received as a blob

defs.name: ArrayBuffer
defs.docs: Binary message received as an array buffer

defs.name: SocketMessageData
defs.docs:
Represents the types of data which can be received on a web socket. Messages
 are transmitted tagged as either binary or text: text messages are always
 received as strings. Binary messages may be received as either blobs or array
 buffers as preferred by the receiver. This choice is indicated via the
 `binary_type` field on the web socket.

defs.name: into_text
defs.docs: Try to receive the message as text

defs.name: into_blob
defs.docs: Try to receive the message as a binary blob

defs.name: into_array_buffer
defs.docs: Try to receive the message as an array buffer

defs.name: IMessageEvent
defs.docs: The MessageEvent interface represents a message received by a target object.

defs.name: Data
defs.docs: The type of data received with this MessageEvent

defs.name: data
defs.docs: The data sent by the message emitter.

defs.name: origin
defs.docs: A string representing the origin of the message emitter.

defs.name: last_event_id
defs.docs: A string representing a unique ID for the event.

defs.name: source
defs.docs:
A MessageEventSource (which can be a WindowProxy, MessagePort, or ServiceWorker object)
 representing the message emitter.

defs.name: ports
defs.docs:
An array of MessagePort objects representing the ports associated with the channel the
 message is being sent through (where appropriate, e.g. in channel messaging or when sending
 a message to a shared worker).

defs.name: SocketMessageEvent
defs.docs: A message event informs a WebSocket object that a message has been received.

defs.name: SlotChangeEvent
defs.docs:
The `slotchange` event is fired on an HTMLSlotElement instance
 (`<slot>` element) when the node(s) contained in that slot change.

defs.name: ITouchEvent
defs.docs:
The `ITouchEvent` interface represents events that occur due to the user
 interacting with a touch device (such as a phone).

defs.name: alt_key
defs.docs: Returns whether the Alt key was down when this event was fired.

defs.name: ctrl_key
defs.docs: Indicates whether the Ctrl key was down when this event fired.

defs.name: meta_key
defs.docs: Indicates whether the Meta key was down when this event fired.

defs.name: shift_key
defs.docs: Indicates whether the Shift key was down when this event was fired.

defs.name: touches
defs.docs: A list of Touches for every point of contact currently touching the surface.

defs.name: target_touches
defs.docs:
A list of Touches for every point of contact that is touching the surface and started
 on the element that is the target of the current event.

defs.name: changed_touches
defs.docs: A list of Touches, one for each touch touch point that just became active with the current event.

defs.name: TouchEvent
defs.docs:
A reference to a JavaScript object which implements the [ITouchEvent](trait.ITouchEvent.html)
 interface.

defs.name: TouchMove
defs.docs:
The `TouchMove` is fired when one or more touch points are moved along the
 touch surface.

defs.name: TouchLeave
defs.docs:
The `TouchLeave` event is fired when a touch point is moved off the
 interactive area of an element.

defs.name: TouchEnter
defs.docs:
The `TouchEnter` event is fired when a touch point is moved onto the
 interactive area of an element.

defs.name: TouchEnd
defs.docs:
The `TouchEnd` event is fired when one or more touch points are removed
 from the touch surface.

defs.name: TouchCancel
defs.docs:
The `TouchCancel` event is fired when one or more touch points have been
 disrupted in an implementation-specific manner (for example, too many touch
 points are created).

defs.name: TouchStart
defs.docs:
The `TouchStart` event is fired when one or more touch points are placed
 on the touch surface.

defs.name: IParentNode
defs.docs:
The `ParentNode` mixin contains methods and properties
 that are common to all types of `Node` objects that can
 have children.

defs.name: query_selector
defs.docs:
Returns the first element that is a descendant of the element on which it is
 invoked that matches the specified group of selectors.

defs.name: query_selector_all
defs.docs:
Returns a non-live [NodeList](struct.NodeList.html) of all elements descended
 from the element on which it is invoked that matches the specified group of CSS selectors.

defs.name: INonElementParentNode
defs.docs:
The `INonElementParentNode` mixin contains methods and properties
 that are common to `Document` and `DocumentFragment`.

defs.name: get_element_by_id
defs.docs:
Returns a reference to the element by its ID; the ID is a string which can
 be used to uniquely identify the element, found in the HTML `id` attribute.

defs.name: HtmlCollection
defs.docs:
The `HtmlCollection` interface represents a generic collection
 (array-like object similar to arguments) of elements (in document order)
 and offers methods and properties for selecting from the list.
 
 An `HtmlCollection` in the HTML DOM is live; it is automatically
 updated when the underlying document is changed.
 
 [(JavaScript docs)](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLCollection)

defs.name: len
defs.docs: Returns the number of elements in the collection.

defs.name: item
defs.docs: Returns an element from an `HtmlCollection` by index.

defs.name: iter
defs.docs: Returns an iterator over the collection.

defs.name: IChildNode
defs.docs:
The `ChildNode` interface contains methods that are particular to `Node`
 objects that can have a parent.

defs.name: remove
defs.docs: The `ChildNode.remove()` method removes the object from the tree it belongs to.

defs.name: NoMapping
defs.docs: No mapping is in use for this gamepad

defs.name: Standard
defs.docs: This gamepad is mapped to the [Standard Gamepad layout](https://w3c.github.io/gamepad/#remapping)

defs.name: GamepadMappingType
defs.docs: The set of known gamepad layout mappings.

defs.name: GamepadButton
defs.docs: The state of an individual button on a gamepad device.

defs.name: pressed
defs.docs: Is the button currently pressed?

defs.name: touched
defs.docs: Is the button currently touched?

defs.name: value
defs.docs: The amount which the button has been pressed, between 0.0 (not pressed), and 1.0 (fully pressed).

defs.name: Gamepad
defs.docs: An individual gamepad/controller.

defs.name: id
defs.docs: A string containing some information about this gamepad.

defs.name: index
defs.docs: An auto-incrementing integer to uniquely identify a connected Gamepad.

defs.name: connected
defs.docs: Is this gamepad connected to the system, powered on, and usable?

defs.name: timestamp
defs.docs: Monotonically increasing time this gamepad was updated.

defs.name: mapping
defs.docs: The mapping in use for this device.

defs.name: axes
defs.docs: Array of values for all axes of the gamepad.

defs.name: buttons
defs.docs: Array of button states for all buttons of the gamepad.

defs.name: get_all
defs.docs: Retrieve all connected gamepads, in an array indexed by each gamepad's `index` member.

defs.name: SelectionType
defs.docs: Possible values are:

defs.name: Selection
defs.docs:
Represents the range of text selected by the user or the current position of the caret. To
 obtain a Selection object for examination or modification, call
 [Window.get_selection()](struct.Window.html#method.get_selection).

defs.name: anchor_node
defs.docs: Returns the [Node](struct.Node.html) in which the selection begins.

defs.name: anchor_offset
defs.docs:
Returns the number of characters that the selection's anchor is offset within the
 [anchor_node](struct.Selection.html#method.anchor_node).

defs.name: focus_node
defs.docs: Returns the [Node](struct.Node.html) in which the selection ends.

defs.name: focus_offset
defs.docs:
Returns the number of characters that the selection's anchor is offset within the
 [focus_node](struct.Selection.html#method.focus_node).

defs.name: is_collapsed
defs.docs:
Returns a boolean which indicates whether or not there is currently any text selected; That
 is to say that the selection's start and end points are at the same position in the
 content.

defs.name: range_count
defs.docs: Returns the number of ranges in the selection.

defs.name: kind
defs.docs: Returns the type of the current selection.

defs.name: get_range_at
